article.description: — Garrick Green had a career-high 28 points as Coastal Carolina topped South Alabama 83-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Green carries Coastal Carolina over South Alabama 83-69
article.linkText: Green carries Coastal Carolina over South Alabama 83-69
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — Garrick Green had a career-high 28 points as Coastal Carolina topped South Alabama 83-69 on Saturday. Tyrik Dixon had 18 points for Coastal Carolina (9-2, 3-1 Sun Belt Conference). DeVante’ Jones added 14 points. Essam Mostafa had 10 points, 14 rebounds and four blocks. Coastal Carolina posted a season-high 16 3-pointers. Michael Flowers tied a season high with 29 points for the Jaguars (7-6, 1-3). Tyreke Locure added 11 points and six steals. Sam Iorio had 10 points. The Chanticleers improve to 2-0 against the Jaguars on the season. Coastal Carolina defeated South Alabama 78-65 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
